
[1]permanency

   PER'MANENCY, n. [See Permanent.] Continuance in the same state, or
   without a change that destroys the form or nature of a thing; duration;
   fixedness; as the permanence of a government or state; the permanence
   of institutions or of a system of principles.

   1. Continuance in the same place or at rest.
